1
00:00:02,600 --> 00:00:03,829
<i>My name is Barry Allen,</i>

2
00:00:03,920 --> 00:00:05,434
<i>and I am
the fastest man alive.</i>

3
00:00:06,200 --> 00:00:07,200
<i>To the outside world,</i>

4
00:00:07,280 --> 00:00:09,192
<i>I'm an ordinary
forensic scientist.</i>

5
00:00:09,320 --> 00:00:10,595
<i>But secretly, with the help</i>

6
00:00:10,680 --> 00:00:12,319
<i>of my friends
at S.T.A.R. Labs,</i>

7
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:13,960
<i>I fight crime
and find other meta-humans</i>

8
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,150
<i>like me.</i>

9
00:00:15,240 --> 00:00:17,136
<i>But when my daughter came back
from the future to help,</i>

10
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:19,880
<i>she changed the present</i>

11
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:22,475
<i>and now our world is
more dangerous than ever.</i>

12
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:24,870
<i>And I'm the only one
fast enough to save it.</i>

13
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:27,435
<i>I am the Flash.</i>

14
00:00:28,360 --> 00:00:29,536
<i>Previously on</i> The Flash...

15
00:00:29,560 --> 00:00:31,597
<i>Meet Joss Jackam.</i>

16
00:00:31,680 --> 00:00:34,195
<i>She's a delinquent teen
turned amateur storm chaser.</i>

17
00:00:34,280 --> 00:00:36,556
<i>That weathervane,
doesn't it look a lot like...</i>

18
00:00:36,680 --> 00:00:38,240
<i>The staff
she was carrying, yeah.</i>

19
00:00:38,280 --> 00:00:41,159
<i>It's infected
with a satellite shard.</i>

20
00:00:41,240 --> 00:00:43,311
Our satellite didn't
just create new metas.

21
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:44,400
It created meta-tech.

22
00:00:46,040 --> 00:00:47,872
Every time you vibe
or breach,

23
00:00:47,960 --> 00:00:49,256
the dark matter
is going to affect

24
00:00:49,280 --> 00:00:50,656
your central nervous system,
causing you

25
00:00:50,680 --> 00:00:52,034
<i>more and more pain.</i>

26
00:00:52,120 --> 00:00:53,918
- We need to talk.
<i>- Yes, Nora.</i>

27
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,514
Yes, we do.

28
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:02,631
You've been gone
a long time, Nora.

29
00:01:02,720 --> 00:01:04,518
You're lucky
I came back at all.

30
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:05,600
Really?

31
00:01:10,960 --> 00:01:12,872
I can tell you have questions.

32
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:15,834
Ask them.

33
00:01:15,920 --> 00:01:17,957
- You killed my grandmother?
- I did.

34
00:01:18,040 --> 00:01:19,554
- In front of my father?
- I did.

35
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:20,680
- He was a boy.
- Nora...

36
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:23,036
He was just a kid!

37
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:24,315
You're right,

38
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:28,076
and I think of
that moment every day,

39
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:30,595
how it changed
the course of destiny

40
00:01:30,680 --> 00:01:31,955
for him,

41
00:01:32,040 --> 00:01:33,554
<i>for you,</i>

42
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:34,915
for me.

43
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,799
I never knew he had that kind
of hatred inside of him,

44
00:01:37,880 --> 00:01:40,349
but he does because of you.

45
00:01:40,440 --> 00:01:43,558
And I have that same hatred
inside of me for him!

46
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:47,478
Or at least I did.

47
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:50,951
I was inspired by him,
as you are.

48
00:01:51,040 --> 00:01:53,635
I wanted to know him,
as you do.

49
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:57,191
I wanted to be him.
I wanted to be the Flash.

50
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:59,920
You will never be the Flash.

51
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,150
Exactly!

52
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:05,719
And that realization
is what broke me.

53
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:09,232
<i>That's the realization
that led me to do</i>

54
00:02:09,320 --> 00:02:10,720
<i>the things that I did.</i>

55
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:13,918
The terrible, horrible,

56
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,311
evil things I did.

57
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:20,154
I've been coming here
for so long.

58
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:21,959
Why didn't you tell me
what you did?

59
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:23,520
I thought you must know.

60
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:25,159
Your mother would've told you.

61
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:28,352
I was wrong. I see that.

62
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:31,751
I'm sorry, Nora.

63
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:33,712
I don't trust you anymore.

64
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:35,957
Have I not
given you everything?

65
00:02:36,440 --> 00:02:39,114
<i>The chance to go back and know
a father you never knew?</i>

66
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:41,396
<i>To learn from him?
To run with him?</i>

67
00:02:41,480 --> 00:02:43,278
To run with the Flash.

68
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:47,149
I showed you how
to time travel because...

69
00:02:48,080 --> 00:02:49,833
I want to help you.

70
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:52,435
No, the only person that you
ever help is yourself.

71
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:54,079
Who told you that?

72
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:55,480
Your father?

73
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:03,471
For as long as I can remember,

74
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:05,791
<i>all I ever thought about
was myself,</i>

75
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:07,439
and that will not
be my legacy.

76
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,591
That will not the legacy
of Eobard Thawne!

77
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:10,680
Let me help you!

78
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:15,595
I don't want your help.

79
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:16,830
Not anymore.

80
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:35,756
<i>So we've got some good
news and some bad news.</i>

81
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:38,036
The good news is that CCPD
is still stationed outside

82
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:40,999
of Grace's room and will remain
so until Dwyer's been caught.

83
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:42,799
But the bad news is,
that means Dwyer won't

84
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:44,216
be visiting her again
anytime soon.

85
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,616
<i>And then the worst news is,</i>

86
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:47,552
